 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE 1- &lt;i&gt;The Company and Summary of Significant Accounting Policies:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3188&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;The consolidated financial statements include the accounts of the Company and its subsidiaries
 all of which are wholly-owned. All inter-company transactions have been eliminated.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3190&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Use of estimates and assumptions&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3192&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;The preparation of financial statements in conformity with generally accepted accounting principles requires management to make certain estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities and disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the financial statements
 as well as the reported revenues and expenses during the respective reporting periods. Actual results could differ from those estimates. Amounts estimated related to liabilities for pension benefits
&amp;#160;self-insured workers&amp;#8217; compensation and&amp;#160;employee healthcare benefits&amp;#160;are subject to inherent uncertainties and these estimated liabilities may ultimately settle at amounts which may vary from current estimates. Other areas with underlying estimates include realization of deferred tax assets
 cash surrender or contract value of life insurance policies
 promotional allowances and the
      allowance for doubtful accounts and inventory reserves.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Management believes its current estimates are reasonable and based on the best information available at the time.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3194&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We test long-lived assets for recoverability whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount may not be recoverable. If an impairment is indicated
 we measure the fair value of assets to determine if and when adjustments are recorded.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3196&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Subsequent events&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3198&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Management has evaluated events subsequent to November 1
 2013 through the date the accompanying consolidated financial statements were filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission for transactions and other events that may require adjustment of and/or disclosure in such financial statements. Based on its review
 no material events were identified that require adjustment to the financial statements or additional disclosure.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3200&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Concentrations of credit risk&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3202&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Our credit risk is diversified across a broad range of customers and geographic regions. Losses due to credit risk have recently been immaterial. The carrying amount of cash equivalents
 accounts and other receivables
 accounts payable and accrued liabilities approximate fair market value due to the short maturity of these instruments. We maintain cash balances at financial institutions
 which may at times exceed the amounts insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Management does not believe there is significant credit risk associated with these financial institutions. The provision for doubtful accounts receivable is based on historical trends and current collectability risk. We have significant accounts receivable with a few large
 well known customers which
 although historically secure
 could be subject to material risk should these customers&amp;#8217; operations suddenly
      deteriorate. Sales to Wal-Mart&amp;#174; comprised 19.6% of revenues in fiscal 2013 and 17.0% of total&amp;#160;accounts receivable was due from Wal-Mart&amp;#174; at November 1
 2013. Sales to Dollar General&amp;#174; comprised 9.9% of revenues for fiscal year 2013 and 20.7% of total accounts receivable was due from Dollar General at November 1
 2013. Sales to Wal-Mart&amp;#174; comprised 16.3% of revenues in fiscal 2012 and 19.7% of total&amp;#160;accounts receivable was due from Wal-Mart&amp;#174; at November 2
 2012.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3204&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Business segments&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3206&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Our Company and its subsidiaries operate in two business segments - the processing and distribution of frozen foods
 and the processing and distribution of refrigerated and snack food products.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;See Note 7 to the Consolidated Financial Statements for further information.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3214&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fiscal year&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3216&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We maintain our accounting records on a 52-53 week fiscal basis ending on the Friday closest to October 31. As part of the regular accounting cycle
 fiscal year 2013 included 52 weeks and fiscal year 2012 included 53 weeks.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3218&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Revenues&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3220&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Revenues are recognized upon passage of title to the customer
 typically upon product pick-up
 shipment or delivery to customers. Products are delivered to customers primarily through our own long-haul fleet or through a Company owned direct store delivery system. These delivery costs
 $5
214 and $4
988&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;for 2013 and 2012
 respectively
 are included in selling
 general and administrative expenses in the accompanying consolidated financial statements.&amp;#160; The Company also used independent distributors to deliver products in remote geographic areas of the country.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Revenues are recognized upon shipment to the distributor
 net of return allowances.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Historically
 returns from distributors have been minimal.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The distributor pays for these products in full
 typically within 15 days
 and&lt;/font&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;such payment is not contingent upon payment from the large chain stores.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;As a convenience to certain large chain stores
 we bill these customers on behalf of the distributor. The Company discontinued product distribution through independent third-party distributors in the last quarter of fiscal 2012 in favor of utilizing customer managed warehouse distribution centers.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3222&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We record promotional and returns allowances based on recent and historical trends.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Revenue is recognized as the net amount estimated to be received after deducting estimated amounts for discounts
 trade allowances and product returns.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Promotional allowances
 including customer incentive and trade promotion activities
 are recorded as a reduction to sales based on amounts estimated being due to customers
 based primarily on historical utilization and redemption rates.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Promotional allowances deducted from sales for fiscal years 2013 and 2012 were $8
988 and $7
968&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3224&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Advertising expenses&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3226&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Advertising and other promotional expenses are recorded as selling
 general and administrative expenses.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Advertising expenses for fiscal years 2013 and 2012 were $3
325 and $3
857
 respectively&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3228&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cash and cash equivalents&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3230&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We consider all investments with original maturities of three months or less to be cash equivalents. Cash equivalents include money market funds and treasury bills. Cash equivalents totaled $8
325 at November 1
 2013 and $9
744 at November 2
 2012. All cash and cash equivalents at November 1
 2013 were held at Wells Fargo Bank N.A.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3232&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fair value measurements&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3234&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We classify levels of inputs to measure the fair value of financial assets as follows:&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table style=&quot;TEXT-INDENT: 0px; WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot; id=&quot;TBL5521&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 18pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p id=&quot;PARA5522&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&amp;#9679;&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p id=&quot;PARA5523&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Level 1 inputs: Level 1 inputs are quoted market prices in active markets for identical assets or liabilities that are accessible at the measurement date.&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table style=&quot;TEXT-INDENT: 0px; WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot; id=&quot;TBL3242&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 18pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3240&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&amp;#9679;&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3241&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Level 2 inputs: Level 2 inputs are from other than quoted market prices included in Level 1 that are observable for the asset or liability
 either directly or indirectly.&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table style=&quot;TEXT-INDENT: 0px; WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot; id=&quot;TBL3246&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 18pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3244&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&amp;#9679;&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3245&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Level 3 inputs: Level 3 inputs are unobservable and should be used to measure fair value to the extent that observable inputs are not available.&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3248&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;The hierarchy noted above requires us to minimize the use of unobservable inputs and to use observable market data
 if available
 when determining fair value.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3257&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Inventories&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3259&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Inventories are valued at the lower of cost (which approximates actual cost on a first-in
 first-out basis) or market.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Costs related to warehousing
 transportation and distribution to customers are considered when computing market value.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Inventories include the cost of raw materials
 labor and manufacturing overhead.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;We regularly review inventory quantities on hand and write down any excess or obsolete inventories to net realizable value.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;An inventory reserve is created when potentially slow-moving or obsolete inventories are identified in order to reflect the appropriate inventory value.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Changes in economic conditions
 production requirements
 and lower than expected customer demand could result in additional obsolete or slow-moving inventory that cannot be sold or must be sold at reduced prices and could result in additional reserve
      provisions.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3261&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Property
 plant and equipment&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3263&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Property
 plant and equipment are carried at cost less accumulated depreciation. Major renewals and improvements are charged to the asset accounts while the cost of maintenance and repairs is charged to expense as incurred. When assets are sold or otherwise disposed of
 the cost and accumulated depreciation are removed from the respective accounts and the resulting gain or loss is credited or charged to income. Depreciation is computed on a straight-line basis over 10 to 20 years for buildings and improvements
 5 to 10 years for machinery and equipment
 and 3 to 5 years for transportation equipment.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3265&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Capital Leases&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3267&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Leased property and equipment that meet capital lease criteria are capitalized at the lower of the present value of the minimum payments required under the lease or the fair value of the asset at inception of the lease and are included within property plant and equipment on the consolidated balance sheet. Obligations under capital leases are accounted for as current and noncurrent liabilities on the consolidated balance sheet. Amortization is calculated on a straight-line method based upon the shorter of the estimated useful life of the asset or the lease term.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3269&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Life insurance policies&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3271&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We record the cash surrender value or contract value for life insurance policies as an adjustment of premiums paid in determining the expense or income to be recognized under the contract for the period.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3273&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Income taxes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3275&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Deferred taxes are provided for items whose financial and tax bases differ. A valuation allowance is provided against deferred tax assets when it is expected that it is more likely than not that the related asset will not be fully realized. During the fourth quarter of fiscal 2008
 management recorded a full valuation allowance with respect to its deferred tax assets.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The determination as to whether or not a deferred tax asset can be fully realized is subject to a significant degree of judgment
 based at least partially upon a projection of future taxable income
 which takes into consideration past and future trends in profitability
 customer demand
 supply costs
 and multiple other factors
 none of which are predictable.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3277&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We provide tax accruals for federal
 state
 local and international exposures relating to audit results
 tax planning initiatives and compliance responsibilities. The development of these accruals requires judgments about tax issues
 potential outcomes and timing. (See Note 4 to the Consolidated Financial Statements). Although the outcome of these tax audits is uncertain
 in management&amp;#8217;s opinion adequate provisions for income taxes have been made for potential liabilities emanating from these reviews. If actual outcomes differ materially from these estimates
 they could have a material impact on our results of operations.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3279&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Stock-based compensation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3281&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We measure and recognize compensation expense for all share-based payments to employees
 including grants of employee stock options
 in the financial statements based on the fair value at the date of the grant.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;We have not issued
 awarded
 granted or entered into any stock-based payment agreements since April&amp;#160;29
 1999.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3289&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Foreign currency transactions&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3291&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Our foreign branch located in Canada enters into transactions that are denominated in a foreign currency. The related transaction gains and losses arising from changes in exchange rates are not material and are included in selling
 general and administrative expenses in the consolidated statements of operations in the period the transaction occurred.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3293&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Comprehensive income (loss)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3295&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Comprehensive income (loss) consists of net income and additional minimum pension liability adjustments.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3297&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Recently issued accounting pronouncements and regulations&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3299&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;In July 2013
 the Financial Accounting Standards Board (&quot;FASB&quot;)&amp;#160;issued guidance on Income Taxes for &amp;#8220;Presentation of an Unrecognized Tax Benefit When a Net Operating Loss Carryforward
 a Similar Tax Loss
 or a Tax Credit Carryforward Exists.&amp;#8221; This guidance requires that financial statements reflect a deferred tax asset for a net operating loss carryforward
 a similar tax loss
 or a tax credit carryforward as reduced by any unrecognized tax benefit
 or a portion of an unrecognized tax benefit. The updated guidance is effective for the Company&apos;s interim and annual periods beginning after December 15
 2013
 which will be effective for us beginning fiscal 2015.&amp;#160;We do not expect the adoption of this guidance to have a significant impact on our consolidated financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;


 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Use of estimates and assumptions&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3192&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;The preparation of financial statements in conformity with generally accepted accounting principles requires management to make certain estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities and disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the financial statements
 as well as the reported revenues and expenses during the respective reporting periods. Actual results could differ from those estimates. Amounts estimated related to liabilities for pension benefits
&amp;#160;self-insured workers&amp;#8217; compensation and&amp;#160;employee healthcare benefits&amp;#160;are subject to inherent uncertainties and these estimated liabilities may ultimately settle at amounts which may vary from current estimates. Other areas with underlying estimates include realization of deferred tax assets
 cash surrender or contract value of life insurance policies
 promotional allowances and the
      allowance for doubtful accounts and inventory reserves.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Management believes its current estimates are reasonable and based on the best information available at the time.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3194&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We test long-lived assets for recoverability whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount may not be recoverable. If an impairment is indicated

 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Subsequent events&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3198&quot;&gt;

 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Management has evaluated events subsequent to November 1
 2013 through the date the accompanying consolidated financial statements were filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission for transactions and other events that may require adjustment of and/or disclosure in such financial statements. Based on its review


 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Concentrations of credit risk&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3202&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Our credit risk is diversified across a broad range of customers and geographic regions. Losses due to credit risk have recently been immaterial. The carrying amount of cash equivalents
 accounts and other receivables
 accounts payable and accrued liabilities approximate fair market value due to the short maturity of these instruments. We maintain cash balances at financial institutions
 which may at times exceed the amounts insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Management does not believe there is significant credit risk associated with these financial institutions. The provision for doubtful accounts receivable is based on historical trends and current collectability risk. We have significant accounts receivable with a few large
 well known customers which
 although historically secure
 could be subject to material risk should these customers&amp;#8217; operations suddenly
      deteriorate. Sales to Wal-Mart&amp;#174; comprised 19.6% of revenues in fiscal 2013 and 17.0% of total&amp;#160;accounts receivable was due from Wal-Mart&amp;#174; at November 1
 2013. Sales to Dollar General&amp;#174; comprised 9.9% of revenues for fiscal year 2013 and 20.7% of total accounts receivable was due from Dollar General at November 1
 2013. Sales to Wal-Mart&amp;#174; comprised 16.3% of revenues in fiscal 2012 and 19.7% of total&amp;#160;accounts receivable was due from Wal-Mart&amp;#174; at November 2

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We maintain our accounting records on a 52-53 week fiscal basis ending on the Friday closest to October 31. As part of the regular accounting cycle


 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Revenues&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3220&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Revenues are recognized upon passage of title to the customer
 typically upon product pick-up
 shipment or delivery to customers. Products are delivered to customers primarily through our own long-haul fleet or through a Company owned direct store delivery system. These delivery costs
 $5
214 and $4
988&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;for 2013 and 2012
 respectively
 are included in selling
 general and administrative expenses in the accompanying consolidated financial statements.&amp;#160; The Company also used independent distributors to deliver products in remote geographic areas of the country.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Revenues are recognized upon shipment to the distributor
 net of return allowances.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Historically
 returns from distributors have been minimal.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The distributor pays for these products in full
 typically within 15 days
 and&lt;/font&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;such payment is not contingent upon payment from the large chain stores.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;As a convenience to certain large chain stores
 we bill these customers on behalf of the distributor. The Company discontinued product distribution through independent third-party distributors in the last quarter of fiscal 2012 in favor of utilizing customer managed warehouse distribution centers.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3222&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We record promotional and returns allowances based on recent and historical trends.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Revenue is recognized as the net amount estimated to be received after deducting estimated amounts for discounts
 trade allowances and product returns.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Promotional allowances
 including customer incentive and trade promotion activities
 are recorded as a reduction to sales based on amounts estimated being due to customers
 based primarily on historical utilization and redemption rates.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Promotional allowances deducted from sales for fiscal years 2013 and 2012 were $8
988 and $7
968&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;

 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fair value measurements&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3234&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We classify levels of inputs to measure the fair value of financial assets as follows:&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table style=&quot;TEXT-INDENT: 0px; WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot; id=&quot;TBL5521&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 18pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p id=&quot;PARA5522&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&amp;#9679;&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p id=&quot;PARA5523&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Level 1 inputs: Level 1 inputs are quoted market prices in active markets for identical assets or liabilities that are accessible at the measurement date.&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table style=&quot;TEXT-INDENT: 0px; WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot; id=&quot;TBL3242&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 18pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3240&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&amp;#9679;&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3241&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Level 2 inputs: Level 2 inputs are from other than quoted market prices included in Level 1 that are observable for the asset or liability
 either directly or indirectly.&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table style=&quot;TEXT-INDENT: 0px; WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot; id=&quot;TBL3246&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;WIDTH: 18pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3244&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&amp;#9679;&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;VERTICAL-ALIGN: top&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3245&quot;&gt;
            &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Level 3 inputs: Level 3 inputs are unobservable and should be used to measure fair value to the extent that observable inputs are not available.&lt;/font&gt;
          &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3248&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;The hierarchy noted above requires us to minimize the use of unobservable inputs and to use observable market data
 if available


 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Inventories&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3259&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Inventories are valued at the lower of cost (which approximates actual cost on a first-in
 first-out basis) or market.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Costs related to warehousing
 transportation and distribution to customers are considered when computing market value.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Inventories include the cost of raw materials
 labor and manufacturing overhead.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;We regularly review inventory quantities on hand and write down any excess or obsolete inventories to net realizable value.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;An inventory reserve is created when potentially slow-moving or obsolete inventories are identified in order to reflect the appropriate inventory value.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Changes in economic conditions
 production requirements
 and lower than expected customer demand could result in additional obsolete or slow-moving inventory that cannot be sold or must be sold at reduced prices and could result in additional reserve


 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Property
 plant and equipment&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3263&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Property
 plant and equipment are carried at cost less accumulated depreciation. Major renewals and improvements are charged to the asset accounts while the cost of maintenance and repairs is charged to expense as incurred. When assets are sold or otherwise disposed of
 the cost and accumulated depreciation are removed from the respective accounts and the resulting gain or loss is credited or charged to income. Depreciation is computed on a straight-line basis over 10 to 20 years for buildings and improvements
 5 to 10 years for machinery and equipment

 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Income taxes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3275&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Deferred taxes are provided for items whose financial and tax bases differ. A valuation allowance is provided against deferred tax assets when it is expected that it is more likely than not that the related asset will not be fully realized. During the fourth quarter of fiscal 2008
 management recorded a full valuation allowance with respect to its deferred tax assets.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The determination as to whether or not a deferred tax asset can be fully realized is subject to a significant degree of judgment
 based at least partially upon a projection of future taxable income
 which takes into consideration past and future trends in profitability
 customer demand
 supply costs
 and multiple other factors
 none of which are predictable.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3277&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We provide tax accruals for federal
 state
 local and international exposures relating to audit results
 tax planning initiatives and compliance responsibilities. The development of these accruals requires judgments about tax issues
 potential outcomes and timing. (See Note 4 to the Consolidated Financial Statements). Although the outcome of these tax audits is uncertain
 in management&amp;#8217;s opinion adequate provisions for income taxes have been made for potential liabilities emanating from these reviews. If actual outcomes differ materially from these estimates

 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Comprehensive income (loss)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3295&quot;&gt;

 Times


 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Recently issued accounting pronouncements and regulations&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3299&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;In July 2013
 the Financial Accounting Standards Board (&quot;FASB&quot;)&amp;#160;issued guidance on Income Taxes for &amp;#8220;Presentation of an Unrecognized Tax Benefit When a Net Operating Loss Carryforward
 a Similar Tax Loss
 or a Tax Credit Carryforward Exists.&amp;#8221; This guidance requires that financial statements reflect a deferred tax asset for a net operating loss carryforward
 a similar tax loss
 or a tax credit carryforward as reduced by any unrecognized tax benefit
 or a portion of an unrecognized tax benefit. The updated guidance is effective for the Company&apos;s interim and annual periods beginning after December 15
 2013

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE 3- &lt;i&gt;Retirement and Other Benefit Plans:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3664&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Noncontributory-Trusteed Defined Benefit Retirement Plans for Sales
 Administrative
 Supervisory and Certain Other Employees&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3666&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We have noncontributory-trusteed defined benefit retirement plans for sales
 administrative
 supervisory and certain other employees. In the third quarter of fiscal 2006
 we froze future benefit accruals under this plan for employees classified within the administrative
 sales or supervisory job classifications or within any non-bargaining class. The benefits under these plans are primarily based on years of service and compensation levels. The funding policy of the plan is to make contributions which are at least equal to the minimum required contributions needed to avoid a funding deficiency. The measurement date for the plan is our fiscal year end.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3668&quot;&gt;

 Times

    &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3923&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;The Company performs an internal rate of return analysis when making the discount rate selection.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The discount rates were based on Citigroup Pension Liability Index as of November 1
 2013 and November 2
 2012
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA3930&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Plan assets are primarily invested in marketable equity securities
 corporate and government debt securities and are administered by an investment management company. The plans&amp;#8217; long-term return on assets is based on the weighted-average of the plans&amp;#8217; investment allocation as of the measurement date and the published historical returns for those types of asset categories
 taking into consideration inflation rate forecasts. Our expected employer contribution to the plan in fiscal year 2014 is $1
693.&lt;/font&gt;

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Executive Retirement Plans&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4172&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Non-Qualified Deferred Compensation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4174&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Effective January&amp;#160;1
 1991 we adopted a deferred compensation savings plan for certain key employees. Under this arrangement
 selected employees contribute a portion of their annual compensation to the plan. We contribute an amount to each participant&amp;#8217;s account by computing an investment return equal to Moody&amp;#8217;s Average Seasoned Bond Rate plus 2%. Employees receive vested amounts upon death
 termination or attainment of retirement age. No benefit expense was recorded under these plans for fiscal years 2013 and 2012.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4176&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4178&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;In fiscal year 1991
 we adopted a non-qualified supplemental retirement plan for certain key employees.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Benefits provided under the plan are equal to 60% of the employee&amp;#8217;s final average earnings
 less amounts provided by our defined benefit pension plan and amounts available through Social Security.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4180&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Benefits payable related to these plans and included in the accompanying consolidated&amp;#160;financial statements were $4
521&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;and $4
997 at November 1
 2013 and November 2
 2012
 respectively. In connection with this arrangement we are the beneficiary of life insurance policies on the lives of certain key employees and retirees. The aggregate cash surrender value of these policies
 included in non-current assets
 was $13
140 and&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;$12
315 at November 1
 2013 and November 2
 2012
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4187&quot;&gt;

        &lt;/td&gt;

    &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4227&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Incentive Compensation Plan for Certain Key Executives&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4229&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We provide an incentive compensation plan for certain key executives
 which is based upon our pretax income. The payment of these amounts is generally deferred over three or five-year periods. The total amount payable related to this arrangement was $1
873 and $1
658&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;at November 1
 2013 and November 2
 2012
 respectively. Future payments are approximately $724
 $677
 $365
 $70 and $37 for fiscal years 2014 through 2018
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4231&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Postretirement Healthcare Benefits for Selected Executive Employees&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4233&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We provide postretirement health care benefits for selected executive employees.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Net periodic postretirement healthcare cost is determined using assumptions as of the beginning of each fiscal year
 except for the total actual benefit payments and the discount rate used to develop the net periodic postretirement benefit expense
 which is determined at the end of the fiscal year.&lt;/font&gt;

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;401(K)&amp;#160;Plan for Sales
 Administrative
 Supervisory and Certain Other Employees&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4554&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;During the fiscal year ended November&amp;#160;3
 2006
 we implemented a qualified 401(K)&amp;#160;retirement plan (the &amp;#8220;Plan&amp;#8221;) for our sales
 administrative
 supervisory and certain other employees. During fiscal years 2013 and 2012
 we made total employer contributions to the Plan in the amounts of&amp;#160;$452 and $442
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;

        &lt;td style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: center; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

          $
        &lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;BORDER-BOTTOM: #000000 3px double; TEXT-ALIGN: right; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff; WIDTH: 14%; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: bottom&quot; id=&quot;TBL4881.finRow.19.amt.3&quot;&gt;
          -
        &lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3px; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff; WIDTH: 1%; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: bottom&quot; id=&quot;TBL4881.finRow.19.trail.3&quot; nowrap=&quot;nowrap&quot;&gt;
          &amp;#160;
        &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4883&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;The Company policy outlines measurable objective criteria that must be met before a release of the valuation allowance will occur.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The three criteria set forth in the policy must all be satisfied before the valuation allowance can be reversed.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The criteria are as follows: first
 the Company&amp;#8217;s available federal tax net operating loss (&quot;NOL&quot;) must be zero; second
 the prior thirty-six month cumulative book basis pre-tax income (loss)
 after considering &amp;#8220;one-time&amp;#8221; events
 is positive;&amp;#160;third
 the Company considers its outlook of near term continued profitable operations and assesses any material negative and positive trends or events on the immediate horizon.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;As of November 1
 2013
 the Company (1) has a federal tax NOL of $1
394
 (2) has positive thirty-six month cumulative book income and (3) commodity costs are trending higher for the fourth quarter of
      fiscal&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;2013 which creates uncertainty about the Company&apos;s ability to generate future earnings.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Only the second criterion has been satisfied
 therefore
 the Company will maintain a full valuation allowance against its deferred tax assets as of November 1
 2013. The weight of negative factors and level of economic uncertainty in our current business continued to support the conclusion that the realization of our deferred tax assets does not meet the more likely than not standard.&amp;#160; Therefore
 a full valuation allowance will remain against the net deferred tax assets.&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4892&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;As of November 1
 2013
 the Company had federal and state net operating loss carryforwards of approximately $1
394 and $3
302 respectively.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;These loss carryforwards will expire at various dates from 2019 through 2033.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4894&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;In July 2006
 the FASB issued guidance to clarify the accounting for uncertainty in income taxes recognized in an enterprise&amp;#8217;s financial statements. This interpretation prescribed a recognition threshold and measurement attribute for the financial statement recognition and measurement of a tax position taken or expected to be taken in a tax return. The guidance also discussed derecognition
 classification
 interest and penalties
 accounting in interim periods
 disclosure
 and transition. The provisions of this guidance have been incorporated into Accounting Standards Codification (&quot;ASC&quot;) 740-10.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4896&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;As of November 1
 2013
 we have provided a liability of $100 for unrecognized tax benefits related to various federal and state income tax matters. This entire amount would reduce our effective income tax rate if the asset is recognized in future reporting periods.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;We have not identified any new unrecognized tax benefits.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4898&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;As of November 2
 2012
 we have provided a liability of $97 for unrecognized tax benefits related to various federal and state income tax matters.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;This entire amount would reduce our effective income tax rate if the asset is recognized in future reporting periods. &amp;#160;We have not identified any new unrecognized tax benefits.&lt;/font&gt;

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We recognize any future accrued interest and penalties related to unrecognized tax benefits in income tax expense.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;As of November 1
 2013
 we had approximately $3 in accrued interest and penalties which is included as a component of the $100 unrecognized tax benefit noted above.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4970&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Our federal income tax returns are open to audit under the statute of limitations for the years ended October 31
 2009 through 2012.&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4972&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We are subject to income tax in California and various other state taxing jurisdictions. Our state income tax returns are open to audit under the statute of limitations for the fiscal years ended October 31
 2009 through 2012.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4974&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We do not anticipate a significant change to the total amount of unrecognized tax benefits within the next 12 months.&lt;/font&gt;

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE 5- &lt;i&gt;Line of Credit:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4978&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We maintain a line of credit with Wells Fargo Bank
 N.A. that expires on&amp;#160;March 1
 2015. Under&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;the terms of this line of credit
 we may borrow up to $2
000 at an interest rate equal to the bank&amp;#8217;s reference rate
 unless we elect an optional interest rate.&amp;#160;The borrowing agreement contains various covenants
 the more significant of which require us to maintain a minimum tangible net worth and a Quick Ratio not less than 1.0 to 1.0
 a minimum net income after tax and total capital expenditures less than $3
000. The Company was in violation of the capital expenditure covenant which was waived (letter dated December 17
 2013). There were no borrowings under this line of credit during the year. The Company is currently in compliance with all provisions of the agreement.&lt;/font&gt;

  
  
  
  
  

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;b&gt;NOTE 6- &lt;i&gt;Contingencies and Commitments:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;The Company leases warehouse and/or office facilities throughout the United States and Canada through month-to-month rental agreements.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 30pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA4988&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;Leases for semi-truck&amp;#160;trailers expire in&amp;#160;2015 and are classified as operating leases.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Six year leases for semi-trucks expire in 2018 and are classified as capital leases.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Rental payments&amp;#160;including prior leases were $581 in 2013 and $554 in 2012. Amortization of equipment under capital lease was $206 in 2013.&lt;/font&gt;

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;(a) Minimum payments&amp;#160;exclude contingent rentals based on actual mileage and adjustments of rental payments based on the Consumer Price Index. Contingent rentals amounted to $127 in 2013 and $122 in 2012 including prior lease arrangements.&lt;/font&gt;

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;(b) Amount necessary to reduce net minimum lease payments to present value calculated at the Company&amp;#8217;s incremental borrowing rate at the inception of the leases.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA5126&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;(c) Reflected in the Note 2
 as current and noncurrent obligations under capital leases of $231 and $1328
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;

      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE 7- &lt;i&gt;Segment Information:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA5134&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We have two reportable operating segments
 Frozen Food Products (the processing and distribution of frozen products)
 and Refrigerated and Snack Food Products (the processing and distribution of refrigerated meat and other convenience foods).&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA5136&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;We evaluate each segment&amp;#8217;s performance based on revenues and operating income. Selling
 general and administrative expenses include corporate accounting
 information systems
 human resource and marketing management at the corporate level. These activities are allocated to each operating segment based on revenues and/or actual usage.&lt;/font&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN: 0pt&quot; id=&quot;PARA5138&quot;&gt;
      &lt;font style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif; FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;&gt;The following segment information is for the fiscal years ended November 1
 2013 (52 weeks) and November 2
 2012 (53 weeks):&lt;/font&gt;

	background-color: #def;
	border: 2px solid #2F4497;
	font-size: 1em;
	position: absolute;
}

	display: block;
	font-weight: bold;
}
..report table.authRefData p {
	margin-top: 0px;
}

	background-color: #2F4497;
	padding: 1px 3px 0px 0px;
	text-align: right;
}
..report table.authRefData .hide a:hover {
	background-color: #2F4497;
}
..report table.authRefData .body {
	height: 150px;
	overflow: auto;
	width: 400px;
}
..report table.authRefData table{
	font-size: 1em;
}
/* Report Styles */
..pl a
 .pl a:visited {
	color: black;
	text-decoration: none;
}
/* table */
..report {
	background-color: white;
	border: 2px solid #acf;
	clear: both;
	color: black;
	font: normal 8pt Helvetica
 Arial
 san-serif;
	margin-bottom: 2em;
}

	border: 1px solid #acf;
}
/* Top labels */

	background-color: #acf;
	color: black;
	font-weight: bold;
	text-align: center;
}

	background-color: transparent;
	color: #000000;
	font: bold 10pt Helvetica
 Arial
 san-serif;
	text-align: left;
}
..report .pl {
	text-align: left;
	vertical-align: top;
	white-space: normal;
	width: 200px;
	word-wrap: break-word;
}
..report td.pl a.a {
	cursor: pointer;
	display: block;
	width: 200px;
	overflow: hidden;
}
..report td.pl div.a {
	width: 200px;
}
..report td.pl a:hover {
	background-color: #ffc;
}
/* Header rows... */

	background-color: #acf;
	color: black;
	font-weight: bold;
}
/* Calendars... */
..report .rc {
	background-color: #f0f0f0;
}
/* Even rows... */

	background-color: #def;
}

	border-bottom: 1px solid black;
}
/* Odd rows... */

	background-color: white;
}

	border-bottom: 1px solid black;
}

	border-bottom: 0px solid black;
}
/* styles for footnote marker */

	white-space: nowrap;
}

	text-align: right;
	white-space: nowrap;

	padding: 0px 0.4em 0px 2em;
}
/* styles for text types */
